On a nightly rustup 1.18.3 (435397f48 2019-05-22)
Some code like this
```
#![feature(existential_type)]
pub trait T {
    fn bla() -> ();
}

pub struct S {
  v: u64
}

impl T for S {
    fn bla() -> () {}
}

existential type TE: T;
pub fn bla() -> TE {
    return S {v:1}
}

pub fn bla2() -> TE {
    bla()
}
```

cause error 

> Compiling playground v0.0.1 (/playground)
> error[E0391]: cycle detected when processing `TE`
>   --> src/lib.rs:14:1
>    |
> 14 | existential type TE: T;
>    | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
>    |
> note: ...which requires processing `bla2`...
>   --> src/lib.rs:19:21
>    |
> 19 |   pub fn bla2() -> TE {
>    |  _____________________^
> 20 | |     bla()
> 21 | | }
>    | |_^
>    = note: ...which again requires processing `TE`, completing the cycle
> note: cycle used when collecting item types in top-level module
>   --> src/lib.rs:1:1
>    |
> 1  | / #![feature(existential_type)]
> 2  | | pub trait T {
> 3  | |     fn bla() -> ();
> 4  | | }
> ...  |
> 20 | |     bla()
> 21 | | }
>    | |_^
> 
> error: concrete type differs from previous defining existential type use
>   --> src/lib.rs:19:1
>    |
> 19 | / pub fn bla2() -> TE {
> 20 | |     bla()
> 21 | | }
>    | |_^ expected `S`, got `TE`
>    |
> note: previous use here
>   --> src/lib.rs:15:1
>    |
> 15 | / pub fn bla() -> TE {
> 16 | |     return S {v:1}
> 17 | | }
>    | |_^
> 
> error: aborting due to 2 previous errors

